>Touch of Bone

This went by with very little fanfare.
I'll blame the thread it was posted in.

I have to admit, when I came across the post, I stopped reading at bone, took a brief glance at the image and scrolled past.
Lucky for me, I read the OP again and saw who actually wrote it and decided to give it a shot.

First of all, the premise is very similar to "other thing".
"Other thing" is my favorite fic however, so I don't mind that one bit.

Enrique is a lot less "restricted" than Leo.
He's curious about his new long stay house guest and enjoys her company after getting over the initial shock.
This makes him a lot easier to relate to him, we all want a fuzzy wife and I'd certainly give a bonedog a shot if she just dropped into my life.

Eva is very friendly for being so untamed and unused to the company of humans.
Her voice mimikry and eagerness to learn speech to talk with Ricky is pretty cute too, interesting it isn't quite clear yet if she can really understand what she is saying herself or if she just goes by his reactions and hopes she gets it right.

I like your interactions between the human and non-human so much, I kinda check out when the MC is going to work, my bad.
He's playing it a little risky talking about her so much under the thin veil of "What would you do if".
Maybe it's for the best when Eva needs a vet for something.

Temptation VS Reclusiveness
It took Leo a long time before he even considered letting Missy get that close, he's still not quite there yet either.

Rick was instantly interested when he saw her in private.
He held himself back, mainly due to not knowing just how much human or animal she really is.
Giving in early and then regretting it right after, with the very infatuated Eva in bed, is a nice cliffhanger and leaves me wanting more.

This felt kinda like a "What if they did things very differently (and were pretty different people too)" take on Hatsssss.
I really enjoyed this, great job!
